<subSubSection id="C348651FFFED774B4AAEFEDC304BFFE1" pageId="21" pageNumber="86" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BED3694FFED774B4AAEFEDC304BFFE1" blockId="21.[151,1437,152,467]" pageId="21" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="B926EA86FFED774B4AAEFEDC345AFFB9" bold="true" box="[199,315,369,395]" pageId="21" pageNumber="86">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C524D17FFED774B4B2AFEDC3710FFB9" authority="Venugopal &amp; Thomas, 2019" authorityName="Venugopal &amp; Thomas" authorityYear="2019" box="[323,625,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pherosophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="devagiriensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B926EA86FFED774B4B2AFEDC3710FFB9" box="[323,625,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="86">Pherosophus devagiriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B926EA86FFED774B4813FEDC37B4FFB9" bold="true" box="[634,725,369,395]" pageId="21" pageNumber="86">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21557FDFFED774B4813FEDC37B4FFB9" box="[634,725,369,395]" pageId="21" pageNumber="86" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D17FFED774B49CCFEDF316AFFB9" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[933,1035,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pheropsophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">
<emphasis id="B926EA86FFED774B49CCFEDF316AFFB9" box="[933,1035,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="86">P. hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from it by head entirely yellow, pronotum with bright yellow spot not reaching the lateral margin, lateral margin black, pronontal median furrow deep, disc glabrous and shiny, elytral humeral spot very small, elytral yellow apical band narrow.
</paragraph>
